  "description": "Variation of conditions 1, 25, 27, 32 and 38 and removal of condition 26 of planning permission dated 02 April 2015 (13/11894/COFUL ) for the redevelopment of Lisson Arches, Penn House and 4 Lilestone Street; namely, the erection of a building at Lisson Arches on Bernhardt Crescent to provide enterprise space (Class B1(b ), (c ), flats for the elderly to replace the accommodation in Penn House. Redevelopment of Penn House and 4 Lilestone Street to prove a new community /health care hub and residential units in buildings with basement car parking off Lilestone Street, public realm/landscaping improvements and other enabling works. (Council's Own Development). \rNAMELY to vary the approved drawing numbers to alter the tenure, change the guest unit at ground floor level to an affordable housing unit, relocation of laundry room, reduction in the size of the entrance lobby and removal of hairdresser and carers room, changes to fenestration, introduction of a mezzanine to create additional enterprise workspace, revised balcony corner at L09 and L10 matching approved detail elsewhere, changes to plant openings at L00 to provide additional ventilation, reduction in flue numbers. revision to L01 terrace design following consultation with residents, changes to plant louvres; minor increase in height to allow for non combustible finishes, amend Condition 25 and 27 to reflect the change from Excellent to a Very Good Rating, deletion of Code for Sustainable Homes, amend the drawing reference in Condition 32 from 1222/01 PG100 rev A to 1222/01 PG100 rev B, amend condition 38 as an increase in Social Rent units to 59, rather than 45 and provision of 1,371 sqm of commercial floorspace rather than 1137 sqm.",
